            "  G   G           Guanine\n"
            "  R   A or G      puRines\n"
            "  Y   C or T      pYrimidines\n"
            "  S   G or C      Strong bonds (3H)\n"
            "  W   A or T      Weak bonds (2H)\n"
            "  K   G or T      Keto\n"
            "  M   A or C      aMino\n"
            "  B   C, G or T   not A\n"
            "  D   A, G or T   not C\n"
            "  H   A, C or T   not G\n"
            "  V   A, C or G   not T\n"
            "  N   A,C,G or T  aNy base\n\n"
            "Example:\n"
            "  ABRE motif  ACGTG  → matches only ACGTG\n"
            "  ERF motif   CCGCC  → all C/G, very specific\n"
            "  Nin-like    WWWTGR → W=A/T, R=A/G, very flexible\n\n"
            "⚠ More IUPAC wildcards = higher random-match probability\n"
            "  = harder to reach significance. This is expected biology,\n"
